A data source may provide any JSON object, unrestriced by the BrAPI specification. type: object crossingProjectName: description: The human readable name for a crossing project type: string example: Crosses_2018 crossingProjectDescription: description: the description for a crossing project type: string example: Crosses between germplasm X and germplasm Y in male nursery study X_2018 and female nursery study Y_2018 programDbId: description: the unique identifier for a program type: string example: a088176c programName: description: the human readable name for a program type: string example: IITA Cassava commonCropName: description: the common name of a crop (for multi-crop systems) type: string example: Cassava potentialParents: description: |- A list of all the potential parents in the crossing block, available in the crossing project
If the parameter 'includePotentialParents' is false, the array 'potentialParents' should be empty, null, or excluded from the response object. type: array items: $ref: '#/components/schemas/CrossParent' externalReferences: $ref: '#/components/schemas/ExternalReferences'
